race.comment: Another strong metropolitan maiden with a few key chances. LIGHT THE NIGHT (3) ran on powerfully in a similar class of maiden last start to finish less than a length from the winner. Holder sticks and with natural improvement, she can win this. STREET LEGAL (5) comes across to SA from Phillip Stokes' Victorian base, where he has been mixing his form. If he can replicate the performance at Pakenham two starts back, he can be in the finish. He will roll forward from a low draw and might be able to control the race. BEL RAGAZZO (1) bumped into a handy filly on debut and is open to improvement second-up. He can run a place, as can SKADOOSH (12) who keeps racing well and is sure to win one of these soon.
